 {"id":"brenner_bot-t62l.4","title":"Task: Document experiment capture workflow + safety model","description":"# Goal
Document what experiment capture does (and does not) guarantee, so operators can use it safely.

---

# Include
- The v0 stance: wrapper-run + capture, not a hardened sandbox
- Safety guidance:
  - only run commands you trust
  - use `--timeout`
  - avoid running against production data
  - be mindful of secrets in env vars
- Failure modes:
  - command fails / exit non-zero
  - timeout
  - huge stdout/stderr (how we handle it)
- Where result files live and how to inspect them
- How capture relates to interpretation (separate step)

---

# Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Operators understand the safety model and failure modes
- [ ] Runbook contains copy/paste examples
